fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.data.types

Interface IIntegerType

  • All Superinterfaces:
    INumberType, IType

    public interface IIntegerType
extends INumberType
    Cell data type representing an integer number type.

    This type supports signed 32-bit and 64-bit integers. To support integers with additional precision, use IDecimalType.

    Thread safety: implementations are required to be immutable and therefore completely thread-safe.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    REFLEXE Technologies

      • getPrecision

        int getPrecision()
        Gets the precision of the integer type as a number of decimal digits. For example, the value 12345 requires a precision of 5.
        Returns:
        the non-negative precision.
        Since:
        1.0

      • isInt32

        boolean isInt32()
        Indicates if the integer type fits into a 32-bit signed integer range. Specifically, indicates if data of this type can be converted (without potential data loss) into a primitive Java int value.
        Returns:
        true if data of this type can be converted (without data loss) into a primitive Java int value, otherwise returns false.
